#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:3
msgid "Stanton SCS.3m “DaMix”"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:6
msgid ""
"[Manufacturer’s product "
"page](https://web.archive.org/web/20221127080207/http://www.stantondj.com/stanton-"
"controllers-systems/scs3m.html)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:10
msgid "Mapping Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:13
msgid "Stanton SCS.3m \"DaMix\" (top view)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:20
msgid ""
"Stanton SCS.3m \"DaMix\" (top view). *Images courtesy of Stanton Magnetics, "
"Inc.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:22
msgid ""
"The left side of the controller controls deck 1. The right side is for deck "
"2. This l’ll walk through the controller from top to bottom and explain the "
"features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:26
msgid "Deck select buttons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:29
msgid ""
"These are used only as modifier buttons in Mixxx for now. Hold them down to "
"access different functions for that side of the controller (Deck A/C for the"
" left side virtual deck 1, Deck B/D for the right side, deck 2,) detailed "
"for each control below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:34
msgid "Top horizontal sliders"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:37
msgid "These adjust the pitch control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:39
msgid ""
"Touching near the edges will do a temporary pitch bend in that direction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:40
msgid ""
"Hold the current mode button down (EQ/FX) and touch the slider on that side "
"to reset it to 0%."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:42
msgid ""
"Hold the applicable Deck select button down when using these sliders to "
"perform fine-grained pitch adjustment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:45
#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:79
msgid "When the Master button is held down:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:47
msgid "The left slider adjusts the Pre/Main headphone mix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:48
msgid "The right slider adjusts main balance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:49
msgid ""
"Also hold the current mode button and touch the slider on that side to reset"
" it to center"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:52
msgid "FX/EQ sliders"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:55
msgid "From left to right, for each side:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:57
msgid "in EQ mode these adjust Low, Mid, and High frequency filters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:58
msgid "in FX mode these adjust Depth, Delay, and LFO for the flanging effect"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:60
msgid ""
"Hold down the current mode button (FX/EQ) and touch one of these sliders to "
"reset it to center."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:63
msgid "FX/EQ mode buttons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:66
msgid ""
"Press these to choose what the sliders above them control. (See above.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:68
msgid "Hold Deck and press FX to toggle the flange effect for that deck"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:69
msgid ""
"Hold Deck and press EQ to auto-adjust the pitch to sync the BPM on this deck"
" with the other one (assuming it was detected correctly on both)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:72
msgid "Volume sliders"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:75
msgid "These adjust the channel volume as on a traditional mixer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:77
msgid "Holding Deck causes these to adjust the pre-fader gain for the deck"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:81
msgid "The left slider adjusts the headphone volume"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:82
msgid "The right slider adjusts main volume"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:84
msgid "Soft buttons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:87
msgid "From top to bottom on both sides:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:89
msgid "Rewind"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:90
msgid "Fast forward"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:91
msgid "Cue"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:92
msgid "Play"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:94
msgid "Headphone buttons toggle that deck in the headphone mix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:96
msgid "Cross-fader"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:99
msgid "Adjusts the cross-fade between the virtual decks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:101
msgid ""
"Needle drop function: Hold a Deck button to use the cross-fader strip to "
"search through the track loaded on that deck"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:104
msgid "Level Meters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:107
msgid ""
"These normally show the pre-fader signal for the respective deck. When "
"holding down the Master button, they show the stereo main output meters: "
"left side for the left channel, right side for the right channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:111
msgid ""
"**NOTE:** The LEDs are calibrated to the VU meters on-screen. If you see a "
"red LED flicker, *you are clipping* and need to reduce the volume or gain to"
" avoid distorted sound and/or speaker damage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:115
msgid "Deck switching buttons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:118
msgid ""
"When touching the “A C” or “B D” buttons, the mixer switches between decks. "
"On the left side, touching “A C” will switch between decks 1 and 3. On the "
"right side, touching “B D” will switch between decks 2 and 4. All controls "
"except for the crossfader then control the selected deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:123
msgid ""
"Connected SCS.3d modules will follow deck changes. For example if you switch"
" from deck 1 to deck 3 on a SCS.3m, all connected SCS.3d modules who are on "
"deck 1 will also switch to deck 3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:127
msgid "EQ mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:130
msgid ""
"This is the standard mixing mode where the three EQ sliders control "
"low/mid/high. The top slider controls the filter knob."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:133
msgid ""
"Touching EQ will return to EQ mode from the FX modes. Holding EQ and "
"touching a slider will reset it to its preset position. (Unfortunately this "
"doesn’t work for FX and MASTER modes.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:137
msgid "FX modes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:140
msgid ""
"Touch one of the four buttons to the side of the gain slider to control one "
"of the effect chains. Top button selects first effect chain and so forth. In"
" this mode, the vertical sliders control the first three knobs of the first "
"effect in the selected effect chain. The top slider controls dry/wet mix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:145
msgid ""
"You can assign FX chains to the deck by holding FX and pressing one of the "
"four buttons next to the gain slider. So to assign FX chain 1 to the current"
" deck, hold FX and press the top button (right below EQ)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:149
msgid ""
"When holding FX, the volume slider can be used to adjust channel gain. Hold "
"FX and slide up to make the channel louder. Hold FX-EQ and touch the gain "
"slider to reset gain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:153
msgid "MASTER mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:156
msgid ""
"When holding the central MASTER button, the left side controls the headphone"
" channel, while the right side controls the main channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:159
msgid "Left top slider: Pre/main mix on headphone"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:160
msgid "Right top slider: main balance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:161
msgid "Left slider: head gain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:162
msgid "Right slider: main gain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/stanton_scs3m.md:163
msgid "Buttons: The buttons assign effects to head and main output"
msgstr ""
